<br>
typically, HP regen isn't too big a deal for Wizards. If you know how to solo (be it root-nuking or quadding) you shouldn't typically get hit. Sure, it happens, but not too much. Also, a typical druid/cleric heal will get you up to full with one blast.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, if you're already above 200int and don't really want to go all the way to 255, mana items and hp items are really nice. More mana obviously to cast more, but also stamina and hp items are very nice since they mean you can take a few more hits after a quad gone bad, or even if you over aggro by mistake.<br>
<br>
Naked, Raakam has around 800 hps. With the items, I get around 1250 hps which I've found _very_ useful. When buffed for raids, I reach about 2.8/3k hps not counting the skin buff. I've eaten a full round of damage from Vindi and survived it. Sure, I promptly got eaten by the next round, but it was still nice to live these extra 5 seconds and perhaps give some clerics time to camp out. The HPs also have enabled me to survive quite some hits from Trakanon, and given enough time for tanks to regain aggro if I'd fugged up.<br>
<br>
So, I'd probably go something like Int, mana, hps, stamina and ac. Not sure what the order will be if we ever determine what affects the criticals, but so far, that's what I'm going for <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Hope this helps!<br>
<br>
-- Raak <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utwiddleotoole.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiddle OToole</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.eskimo.com/~aiken/eq/Twiddle_OToole_bullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Arrrrghh!!! Ahoy!</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/1/02 12:11:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14953.topic&index=23>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.eskimo.com/~aiken/eq/twidsm2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HP regen items!</span><hr size=1> I'm with Raakam, +hp and +sta are the way to go versus regen.  I'd rather have N extra hp to begin with than an item which will regen them afterwards.  The number of times I have survived a dragon clawing me with about 50hp, and the number of times I have zoned to find all my buffs gone (which means I'd have been dead without my +hp items) both indicate to me that it's better to have to regen slowly from 50hp than it is to be full health at your bind point.<br>
