<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   &quot;especially if the question seems to be the wrong question to be asking...What would you tell a warrior looking for mana regenerating items if he or she asked?&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
I don't see how my question is the wrong to ask.  When I do get hit by mobs, I don't want to sit there forever and wait to regen up.  So I want an hp regen item. <br>
<br>
A warrior asking for mana regen items for himself would be silly, since they only have hp, and no mana. Obviously, wizards have both.  I'm sure there are many wizards who have mana regen items, or would want one, for when you do get hit.<br>
